30	/**
31	 * HASHING
32	 *
33	 * Also refer to docs/source/yosys_internals/hashing.rst
34	 *
35	 * The Hasher knows how to hash 32 and 64-bit integers. That's it.
36	 * In the future, it could be expanded to do vectors with SIMD.
37	 *
38	 * The Hasher doesn't know how to hash common standard containers
39	 * and compositions. However, hashlib provides centralized wrappers.
40	 *
41	 * Hashlib doesn't know how to hash silly Yosys-specific types.
42	 * Hashlib doesn't depend on Yosys and can be used standalone.
43	 * Please don't use hashlib standalone for new projects.
44	 * Never directly include kernel/hashlib.h in Yosys code.
45	 * Instead include kernel/yosys_common.h
46	 *
47	 * The hash_ops type is now always left to its default value, derived
48	 * from templated functions through SFINAE. Providing custom ops is
49	 * still supported.
50	 *
51	 * HASH TABLES
52	 *
53	 * We implement associative data structures with separate chaining.
54	 * Linked lists use integers into the indirection hashtable array
55	 * instead of pointers.
56	 */
